root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>6718</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:addr>erct-001S</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-001S.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Restriction of <fr:link
href="erct-0010.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0010">path objects</fr:link> along <fr:link
href="erct-000X.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000X">quasi-inverses</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001S.agda"
type="external">erct-001S.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex>\mathcal {A}</fr:tex> be a <fr:link
href="erct-0010.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0010">path object</fr:link> and let <fr:tex>B</fr:tex> be a type. Given a <fr:link
href="erct-000X.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000X">quasi-inverse</fr:link> function <fr:tex>g \colon  B \to   \mathopen {} \left   \lvert \mathcal {A} \right   \rvert \mathclose {}</fr:tex>, we can restrict the <fr:link
href="erct-0010.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0010">path object</fr:link> <fr:tex>\mathcal {A}</fr:tex> to a <fr:link
href="erct-0010.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0010">path object</fr:link> structure <fr:tex>g^* \mathcal {A}</fr:tex> on <fr:tex>B</fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block">   \begin {aligned}    \mathopen {} \left   \lvert g^* \mathcal {A} \right   \rvert \mathclose {}  &amp;: \equiv  B \\    x  \approx _{ g^* \mathcal {A} }  y &amp;: \equiv  gx  \approx _{ \mathcal {A} }  gy \\     \mathsf {rx}_{ g^* \mathcal {A} } x &amp;: \equiv   \mathsf {rx}_{ \mathcal {A} } \mathopen {} \left ( gx \right ) \mathclose {}    \end {aligned} </fr:tex>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>5988</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>erct-001S</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Fixing <fr:tex>x:B</fr:tex>, we must show that <fr:tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y:B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y:B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y:B \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y:B \right ) \mathclose {} } } gx \approx _{ \mathcal {A} } gy</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>. But this is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">retract</fr:link> of  <fr:tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } gx \approx _{ \mathcal {A} } y</fr:tex>, which is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link> by the univalence of <fr:tex>\mathcal {A}</fr:tex>; thus the result follows from the closure of <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">propositions</fr:link> under <fr:link
href="erct-0025.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-0025">retracts</fr:link> (<fr:ref
addr="erct-0026"
href="erct-0026.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>).</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:contributions></fr:contributions><fr:context></fr:context><fr:related><fr:tree
