type="external">erct-001I.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A type <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is said to be a <fr:em><fr:strong>proposition</fr:strong></fr:em> when every <fr:tex>x:A</fr:tex>, the type <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="erct-001H.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001H">contractible with centre</fr:link> <fr:tex>x</fr:tex>, i.e. all elements of <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> are identified.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="true"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>6714</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>erct-0010</fr:addr><fr:route>erct-0010.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Path object</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>19</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0010.agda"
type="external">erct-0010.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:link
href="erct-004B.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-004B">reflexive graph</fr:link> <fr:tex>\mathcal {A}</fr:tex> is called <fr:em><fr:strong>univalent</fr:strong></fr:em> when for all <fr:tex>x: \mathopen {} \left   \lvert \mathcal {A} \right   \rvert \mathclose {}</fr:tex> the type <fr:tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y: \mathopen {} \left   \lvert \mathcal {A} \right   \rvert \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y: \mathopen {} \left   \lvert \mathcal {A} \right   \rvert \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y: \mathopen {} \left   \lvert \mathcal {A} \right   \rvert \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( y: \mathopen {} \left   \lvert \mathcal {A} \right   \rvert \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} } }  x \approx _{ \mathcal {A} }  y</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>, or (equivalently), is <fr:link
href="erct-001H.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001H">contractible</fr:link> with centre <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {rx}_{ \mathcal {A} } {x} \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>. We shall refer to a univalent <fr:link
href="erct-004B.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-004B">reflexive graph</fr:link> as a <fr:em><fr:strong>path object</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p><fr:p>We will write <fr:tex>\mathsf {PathObj}</fr:tex> for the (large) type of path objects. In our notation, we will at times silently coerce a given path object to its underlying type of vertices.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
